text: Å (or å) is a letter used in the Danish, Norwegian, Swedish and Finnish languages. It is an A with an overring. Å came from the Old Norse vowel á. == Unused letters with Å == * Ǻ == Meanings for Å == * In science, å is used as a short form of angstrom.
